ucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Chiddingstone, Kent, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Uley, Gloucestershire, England":"Uley, Gloucestershire, England","Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Gloucestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Newark on Trent, Nottinghamshire, England":"Newark-on-Trent, Nottinghamshire, England","Ocle Pychard, Herefordshire, England":"Ocle Pychard, Herefordshire, England"},"en":{"about 1340–about 1400":"about 1340–about 1400","1340–1400":"1340–1400","1340–1393":"1340–1393","1370–1488":"1370–1488","1376–1473":"1376–1473","1300–Male":"1300–Deceased","1309–1393":"1309–1393","about 1370":"about 1370","about 1393":"about 1393","1330":"1330","1473":"1473","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1393":"1393","1370":"1370","1488":"1488","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","1376":"1376","25 April 1393":"25 April 1393","about 1400":"about 1400","1309":"1309","about 1340":"about 1340","Uley, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Chiddingstone, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Uley, Gloucestershire, England":"Uley, Gloucestershire, England","Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom","Newark on Trent, Nottinghamshire, England":"Newark-on-Trent, Nottinghamshire, England","Ocle Pychard, Herefordshire, England":"Ocle Pychard, Herefordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bassett","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): from Old French <i>basset</i> ‘of low stature’, a diminutive of <i>basse</i> ‘low, short’, either a nickname for a short person or a status name for someone of humble origins.","Altered form of French   Bessette   1 or <b>Besset</b> (see   Bessette   2).","History: William Bassett (<i>c.</i> 1598–1667) came to Plymouth, MA, from Kent, England, in the 1620s; <i>c.</i> 1650 he moved to Duxbury and subesequently to Bridgewater. He had many prominent descendants, among them one of the earliest families on Martha's Vineyard. — The surname <i>Bassett</i> of French origin (see 2 above) is listed in the register of Huguenot ancestors recognized by the Huguenot Society of America."],"variants":[{"name":"Bessette","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Marcel, Armand, Adrien, Normand, Alphonse, Lucien, Cecile, Herve, Jacques, Laurent, Aime.","French: topographic name designating a small wood of birches, from Occitan <i>bès</i> ‘birch tree’ (see   Besse  ), or a habitational name from (La) Bessette, the name of several places in the southern part of France.","Alternatively, an altered form of French <b>Besset</b>: topographic name, a cognate of 1 above. Altered ending reflects the Canadian and American French practice of sounding the final <i>-t</i>."]}]},{"name":"Symond","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Simon  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Simon","meanings":["Usual English form of   Simeon  , borne in the New Testament by various characters: two apostles, a brother of Jesus, a Pharisee, a leper, a tanner, a sorcerer (who offered money for the gifts of the Holy Ghost, giving rise to the term <i>simony</i>), and the man who carried Jesus's cross to the Crucifixion."]}]},{"name":"Pynchard","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin):","from the Old Norman French personal name <i>Ponchard</i>, Old French <i>Ponsard</i>, a pet form of <i>Ponce</i> (see   Points  ).","habitational name from Pontchardon (in Orne, France), whose name means ‘thistle bridge’."],"variants":[{"name":"Points","meanings":["English (of Norman origin):","from the Old French personal name <i>Ponz</i>, <i>Ponce</i>, from Latin <i>Pontius</i> (see   Ponce  ).","habitational name from any of several places called Ponts (such as those in Manche and in Seine-Maritime, Normandy), from Latin <i>pontes</i> ‘bridges’. This name has been established since the 13th century in Ireland, where it appears as <i>Pounce</i> and <i>Pounche</i>, and is Gaelicized as <b>Púinse</b>."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":42,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Symond Pynchard Bassett was born about 1340, in Uley, Gloucestershire, England, his father, Sir John Pynchard Bassett 1st Lord of Uley, was 42 and his mother, Isabella Ettington Maynell, was 32. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Elizabeth Maud Bytton. He died about 1400, at the age of 62."},"et":{"about 1340–about 1400":"umbes 1340–umbes 1400","1340–1400":"1340–1400","1340–1393":"1340–1393","1370–1488":"1370–1488","1376–1473":"1376–1473","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1309–1393":"1309–1393","about 1370":"umbes 1370","about 1393":"umbes 1393","1330":"1330","1473":"1473","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1393":"1393","1370":"1370","1488":"1488","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","1376":"1376","25 April 1393":"25. aprill 1393","about 1400":"umbes 1400","1309":"1309","about 1340":"umbes 1340","Uley, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Chiddingstone, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Uley, Gloucestershire, England":"Uley, Gloucestershire, England","Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Newark on Trent, Nottinghamshire, England":"Newark-on-Trent, Nottinghamshire, England","Ocle Pychard, Herefordshire, England":"Ocle Pychard, Herefordshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1340–about 1400":"noin 1340–noin 1400","1340–1400":"1340–1400","1340–1393":"1340–1393","1370–1